    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The creature within this tank shudders, and bubbles obscuring its glowing eyes. Thin, flickering fibers emerge from the tank, but dissolve before they can make contact with your temples. One of the beasts has infected the nearby machine and is preventing you from making contact with the creature's mind. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>What will you do?</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Indulge the nevajin's curiosity, and allow it to learn everything it can from the scholar.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>Force the nevajin to kill the buried scholar for what it did. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Instruct the nevajin to silence the scholar, to keep the words from being spoken again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Encourage the nevajin to free the scholar from his prison. He is only a knowledge seeker, after all.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Urge the nevajin to learn the words so it can use their power over others.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank 9</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your own voice speaks directly into the back of your mind. 

"Designate - nevajin. Biomechanical organism with a strong affinity for the Blue Tide. Despite its insatiable curiosity, the nevajin displays an uncanny calm and serenity. It will exchange knowledge for new cyphers or artifacts to examine, but without any indication of greed or goal. They seem single- minded, but so at peace with their pursuits that failure never angers them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>The voice speaks directly into your mind once more. 

"Designate - nevajin. Biomechanical organism with a strong affinity for the Blue Tide. Despite its insatiable curiosity, the nevajin displays an uncanny calm and serenity. It will exchange knowledge for new cyphers or artifacts to examine, but without any indication of greed or goal. They seem single- minded, but so at peace with their pursuits that failure never angers them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine the creature.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Examine the nevajin again. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Leave. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>This tank contains a humanoid with a skull-like head. A name arises from your inherited memories. This is a nevajin, a creature of relentless, overpowering curiosity. Unaware of the Sorrow fragments roaming the platforms, it speaks to itself in a grinding whisper, in a language you don't understand. 

Tendrils of luminescent data snake from the tank and stream into your temples. The room fades in flaring stripes as you enter the mind of the creature in this tank, and see what it sees.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>The presence of the Sorrow fragment in the nearby machine is preventing you from making contact with this creature's mind.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>The tank's data coils reach for you, and draw you carefully back into the mind of the nevajin and the cave with the weeping stone face.

"Only ask," the stone scholar says, fighting every syllable that comes from its lips, "and I will give voice to the eight abominable words that filled Qra's clearwater wells with swarming shadows, and strangled her towers until they fell. Ask, and they will gleefully claim you as well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>The nevajin floats in the tank, silent and still. Nothing more can be gained by entering the creature's mind. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>["I can't do this for you, my friend! Only you can attune your mind to the Tides!"]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Trigger Conv Node 22</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
