    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>The tank's data coils reach for you, and draw you carefully back into the mind of the nevajin and the cave with the weeping stone face.

"Only ask," the stone scholar says, fighting every syllable that comes from its lips, "and I will give voice to the eight abominable words that filled Qra's clearwater wells with swarming shadows, and strangled her towers until they fell. Ask, and they will gladly claim you as well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>The helpless scholar says eight beautiful, alien words that strike the nevajin's mind, fastening to its thoughts like squirming, thorn-covered vines. Concentrating through the pain, the nevajin asks the weeping scholar the first of many questions about lost Qra. 

Later, the nevajin leaves the cave with the words bulging within it, pleased that it has discovered such interesting secrets. 

Warmth spreads through you, aligning Tidal channels in your mind. 
{SCRIPT: +1 Intellect for 3 rounds.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>The scholar finds some reserve of willpower, and shuts its stone mouth, sealing the words within. The nevajin asks question after question about what the scholar knows, but he maintains its noble, agonizing silence.

Eventually, the nevajin leaves the cave and its sole prisoner, disappointed that it was unable to learn ancient secrets that would have brought destruction to everything it loved. 

Warmth spreads through you, aligning Tidal channels in your mind. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>The helpless scholar says eight beautiful, alien words that strike the nevajin's mind, fastening to its thoughts like squirming, thorn-covered vines. Concentrating through the pain, the nevajin asks the weeping scholar the first of many questions about lost Qra. 

